13:38.567 --> 13:41.487
- Not on that goddamn deathtrap.
- Well, suit yourself.

13:41.487 --> 13:43.948
Hey, let me ask you something. You, uh...

13:45.157 --> 13:48.744
You still thinking about that thing
with your cousin, the boat thing?

13:48.744 --> 13:51.205
Yeah, yeah. I got a couple weeks
to let him know.

13:51.205 --> 13:53.624
Been thinking about making a trip
out there maybe next week or

13:53.624 --> 13:56.126
something like that. Check it out.
It's a pretty sweet deal.

13:56.252 --> 13:58.796
Look, you think I haven't thought
about things like that?

13:58.796 --> 14:00.256
I have. Many, many, many times.

14:00.256 --> 14:02.925
But then you think a little bit further,
and you realize, you know,

14:02.925 --> 14:06.178
we may walk amongst normal people.
We can't be out there with them full time.

14:06.178 --> 14:10.474
You know, we gotta be in firehouses.
That's where we're meant to be.

14:10.975 --> 14:13.686
And especially you and me,
our personal lives, man,

14:13.686 --> 14:15.479
it's all the family we got left.

14:15.479 --> 14:17.064
Probie's transferring.

14:21.110 --> 14:23.320
Call Dr. Phil. Maybe he can help.

